<HEADLINE>
<P>
LITHUANIA SUSPENDS ITS INDEPENDENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Your article merely points out that Lithuania is ready to accept the fact that 
without strong American and European political and economic support Lithuania 
is doomed to bleed into economic collapse. 
</P>
<P>
But there's no victory for Gorbachev in this affair, for within a year 
Gorbachev will not be able to enforce any agreements with the republics of the 
Soviet Union because of his diminishing political stature. 
</P>
<P>
The bottom line is simple -- the Russian Empire is crumbling and no Gorbachev 
and no Bush can save it. For Lithuania, Latvia and Estonia are fortunate enough 
to possess qualities which guarantee victory -- intelligence (vision revelance, 
acceptance of reality) -- and emotional intensity (love for freedom and 
independence). 
</P>
<P>
ADOLPH DONINS 
</P>
<P>
Oxnard 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
