<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: GRAF STILL IN SAN DIEGO EVENT, DIRECTOR SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The director for the Great American Bank Tennis tournament said Thursday that 
Steffi Graf will be playing in the San Diego event Aug. 6-12 despite published 
reports that she would take a month off following a sinus operation in 
Heidelberg last Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Jane Stratton said Graf's agent, Philip de Picciotto of Advantage 
International, confirmed Graf would compete in the event following the Players' 
Canadian Open in Montreal July 30- Aug. 5. 
</P>
<P>
Graf has pulled out of the Federation Cup team event in Atlanta starting July 
23. 
</P>
<P>
Graf said at Wimbledon that she had planned the operation for the end of the 
year but was persuaded by doctors to seek an earlier solution to the sinus 
problem that had troubled her for some time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
