</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
RETAIL SALES GROWTH REMAINS SLUGGISH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Price cuts and special promotions boosted business at stores last month, but 
sluggish economic conditions continued to restrain overall retail sales growth, 
according to results released Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Several of the nation's largest retailers posted better June sales than May's 
disappointing tallies. 
</P>
<P>
Despite the rebounds, retail analysts say the industry has been facing a 
difficult period because consumers have been losing confidence in their 
financial well-being and have grown more cautious about spending. 
</P>
<P>
MAJOR RETAILERS' SALES 
</P>
<P>
Sales for the five-week period ending July 7, except as noted. 
</P>
