<P>
E. GERMANY TURNS OVER 2 SUSPECTED TERRORISTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WEST BERLIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two reputed Red Army Faction terrorists were handed over to West German 
authorities Thursday, prosecutors said, after years of sanctuary that may have 
been provided by East Germany's now-disbanded secret police. 
</P>
<P>
Inge Viett and Werner Lotze arrived in the West German city of Karlsruhe, where 
they will appear before an investigating magistrate, according to Rolf Hannich, 
a spokesman for the West German prosecutor's office. 
</P>
<P>
They were among nine alleged Red Army members arrested in East Germany in a 
series of raids last month. 
</P>
