<P>
PAUL LAURENT; FRENCH COMMUNIST PARTY OFFICIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paul Laurent, 65, a senior official of the French Communist Party. Laurent was 
secretary of the party's Central Committee, a member of its Political Bureau 
and a close ally of party leader Georges Marchais. 
</P>
<P>
He also was one of three Communists on the Paris City Council. Last year, he 
led the Communists in negotiations with the governing Socialists to coordinate 
leftist candidacies in municipal elections. Laurent joined the Communist Party 
at age 20. He headed the French Communist youth movement from 1954 to 1962, and 
like many French Communist leaders during the Cold War, was unquestioningly 
faithful to Moscow and had difficulty adapting to less traditional Soviet 
policies. Communist Party candidates now receive less than 10% of votes in 
French elections, compared with double that figure in the immediate postwar 
years. In Paris on Sunday of cancer. 
</P>
