<HEADLINE>
<P>
FLORIDA TEEN-AGER PITCHES TWO 5-INNING NO-HITTERS ON SAME NIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DELAND, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a year of no-hitters, Tom Laraway threw two in one night. 
</P>
<P>
Laraway, 17, was unhittable in both games of an American Legion doubleheader 
Wednesday as the DeLand Chipmunks twice beat Flagler Palm Coast, 10-0, in five 
innings. 
</P>
<P>
Each game was shortened because of the 10-run rule. 
</P>
<P>
"The second game was great," Laraway said. "I had everything working for me. 
The first game was good, but I threw much better the second game." 
</P>
<P>
After the first no-hitter, DeLand Coach Paul Peacock decided to see how far 
Laraway could go in the nightcap. 
</P>
<P>
"Tom has a rubber arm," Peacock said. "He can just keep throwing. His arm was 
feeling great in the second game, so I just told him to go out there and have 
fun. 
</P>
<P>
"He knew he had a chance to make history, but he kept his composure until the 
end. He just went out there and threw strikes." 
</P>
<P>
Flagler hit only two balls hard, both in the second game. A hard grounder down 
the third-base line went foul, and a hard grounder was fielded by the first 
baseman, who made the putout. 
</P>
</TEXT>
