<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 WORKERS DIE IN VAULT BLAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three Pasadena Public Service Department workers were killed Thursday night 
when an explosion rocked an underground electrical vault in Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
The blast occurred shortly before 10:30 p.m. near San Rafael Avenue and La Loma 
Road, said Lori Fitch of the Verdugo dispatch center. The men were pulled from 
the vault about 11 p.m. 
</P>
