<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: CSU REPORTS SHARP RISE IN MINORITY 
ENROLLMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The number of ethnic minorities enrolling in the state university system has 
risen dramatically in recent years and there has been a steady increase in the 
hiring of women and minorities as faculty members, CSU studies released 
Wednesday in Long Beach showed. Between 1984 and 1989, freshmen enrollment 
increased at CSU campuses by 22.6%, while the increases in enrollments of 
under-represented minority groups ranged from 21% to 73%, according to one of 
two reports presented to the CSU Board of Trustees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
