<P>
ELECTRICIAN SUFFERS BURNS FROM CIRCUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TONY MARCANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An electrician sustained first- and second-degree burns in an unoccupied 
building Thursday after he touched a high-power circuit with live current 
running through it, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Brian Phillips, 40, of Huntington Beach was airlifted to UCI Medical Center in 
Orange with burns to his face, arms and chest, hospital spokeswoman Fran 
Tardiff said. He was listed in good condition. 
</P>
<P>
Two co-workers, who were not identified, suffered minor burns in the accident. 
Fire officials said a small blaze was touched off by an arc of electricity in a 
circuit panel. The incident occurred in an area under construction next to the 
South Coast Water Plant at 4905 E. Hunter St. TONY MARCANO 
