<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
1 KILLED OUTSIDE PANORAMA BAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One man was fatally shot and another injured when a fight broke out among 
members of two gangs outside a Panorama City bar early today, Los Angeles 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said about 15 men were leaving Doohinkey's bar at 8929 Woodman Ave. 
about 2 a.m. when a fight broke out in the parking lot. 
</P>
<P>
An unidentified man pulled a gun and fired three or four shots. 
</P>
<P>
Jason Jefferson, 22, of South Los Angeles was struck in the head by a bullet 
and Derrick Potter, 20, also of South Los Angeles, was shot in the hip. 
Jefferson was fatally wounded, Lt. Warren Knowles said. Potter was being 
treated at an undisclosed hospital. 
</P>
<P>
No suspects were arrested in the shooting and the cause of the fight was 
unknown. Members of a gang from Pacoima and a gang from South Los Angeles had 
been in the bar but the groups had no history of being rivals, Knowles said. 
The gunman was believed to be a member of the Pacoima-based gang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
