<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
ISLAMIC GROUP CLAIMS ARCO BLAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
AMMAN, Jordan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An extremist Islamic group today claimed responsibility for an explosion at a 
Texas chemical plant July 5 that killed 17 people. 
</P>
<P>
Arco Chemical Co. of North America said from its headquarters in Newtown 
Square, Pa., that it has not heard of the claim and does not know whether it is 
valid. 
</P>
<P>
The cause of the blast is under investigation, and no signs of sabotage at the 
plant have been reported. 
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Islamic Liberation Front told the Associated Press that the 
Arco plant in Channelview, Tex., was attacked because the United States 
supports Israel despite "its killings and terrorism against our Palestinian 
families" in the occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip. 
</P>
</TEXT>
