<P>
MERCEDES SEEKS TO ADD SHIFTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FRANKFURT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A spokesman for Mercedes-Benz AG confirmed today that the company is 
negotiating with unions to add special shifts at a number of its factories to 
help meet rising demand from East Germany and elsewhere. 
</P>
<P>
The auto-making arm of Daimler-Benz AG, West Germany's largest industrial 
concern, is negotiating with the Workers' Council and unions for permission to 
add weekend shifts. 
</P>
<P>
Attempts to add weekend shifts in January were thwarted by the unions. 
</P>
