<P>
Dr. Arnold Relman plans to retire next year after 14 years as editor of the New 
England Journal of Medicine, the world's leading chronicle of medical research. 
</P>
<P>
Relman, 67, said Thursday he plans to write, teach and lecture after he retires 
next June. 
</P>
<P>
During Relman's tenure, the journal's circulation has grown from 165,000 to 
225,000, the largest paid circulation of any medical journal in the world. It 
was founded in 1812. 
