<P>
VIKINGS SIGN BROWNER FOR 3 YRS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MINNEAPOLIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Minnesota Vikings strong safety Joey Browner has signed three one-year 
contracts averaging more than $900,000 a year, according to a published report 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Vikings General Manager Mike Lynn confirmed that Browner has signed, but he 
would not disclose contract terms. 
</P>
<P>
The Star Tribune, quoting an unidentified source, said Browner signed for 
$850,000 for 1990, $850,000 for 1991 and $1 million for 1992. 
</P>
<P>
The contract also includes a signing bonus but the amount was not known, the 
newspaper said. The contract would make Browner, who has played in the last 
five Pro Bowls, the highest-paid safety in the NFL, the newspaper said. 
</P>
<P>
Browner had been upset for two years about his old contract, which paid him 
$350,000 last season. He tried to renegotiate last summer and repeatedly 
requested a trade. 
</P>
